As I am currently travelling, I do not have access to a build of PHP 8.4-dev with https://github.com/php/php-src/pull/13053. Therefore I cannot check whether `defined('E_STRICT')` and/or `constant('E_STRICT')` also trigger the deprecation. But as these are function calls, we should be able to suppress any `E_DEPRECATED` raised by these using the `@` operator.
